Name: Joe Biden

Name: Joe Biden
Text: To everyone on the front lines of the fight against COVID-19, thank you. We truly couldn't get through this without you.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: As we prepare to reopen America, we have to remember what this crisis has taught us: The administration‚Äôs failure to plan, to prepare, to honestly assess and communicate the threat to the nation led to catastrophic results. We cannot repeat those mistakes. https://t.co/SkfH3U792L

Name: Joe Biden
Text:

Name: Joe Biden
Text: This Easter, Jill and I wish all of you and your families a safe and joyful celebration, and we join our prayers with those of people from every faith for health, happiness, and a renewal of life in the year to come. https://t.co/i3ID9G3qv7

Name: Joe Biden
Text: RT @DrBiden: While our family may be physically distancing, our traditions keep us connected. Ready for Easter! https://t.co/Ay3hkAzlq3

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We are in the middle of a global pandemic ‚Äî and people need access to health care now more than ever. Donald Trump should reopen Obamacare enrollment immediately.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: This new enemy may be unseen, but we have the tools, the expertise, the will, and the spirit to defeat it. There is nothing the American people can't accomplish if we work together.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We need to help as many working families and small businesses as possible. Workers who have lost their jobs or seen their hours slashed and families who are struggling to pay rent and put food on the table need help immediately. There's no time to waste. https://t.co/XFNZK6m1RV

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
We are months into this crisis and our heroes on the front lines still don't have the protective equipment they need to stay safe. It's unconscionable.

Donald Trump needs to fully use the power of the Defense Production Act immediately. https://t.co/wudATlE3wr

Name: Joe Biden
Text: Now more than ever, we have to choose hope over fear, unity over division, truth over lies, and science over fiction.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: President Trump needs to do everything in his power to expand the number of testing sites and surge the number of tests. Mass testing is key to reopening the economy and finding a way out of this crisis. https://t.co/WHprzHoGnm

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The American people are strong, tough, brave, and big-hearted. There's nothing we can't do if we do it together.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: No one should be forced out of their home in the middle of a global pandemic. We need to freeze rent for people who lose their jobs and place a ban on evictions immediately. https://t.co/0sQYpUHosv

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We need a president who demonstrates the leadership to address every aspect of this pandemic‚Ää ‚Äî ‚Ääincluding the spate of racist incidents targeting Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders‚Ää ‚Äî‚Ää with urgency and seriousness. Donald Trump is not that president. https://t.co/4dvq4uiv17

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The folks on the front lines of this crisis are American heroes. https://t.co/ZBwPwiVTL9

Text: La historia de los EE.UU. es la historia de gente com√∫n que hace cosas extraordinarias. S√© que unidos, y como una naci√≥n, nosotros somos m√°s fuertes que este virus. S√© que superaremos esto y seremos m√°s fuertes por ello, se lo prometo. No pierdan la fe. https://t.co/89o4gSMNWF

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
The health inequities being exposed by COVID-19 are unconscionable.

We can do better. We have to. https://t.co/2T1hcOas9z

Name: Joe Biden
Text: Whether you supported Bernie or any other candidate throughout the primary, know that there is a home for you in our campaign. You're not just welcome ‚Äî you're needed. And I will do everything I can to earn your vote this November.

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
America‚Äôs story is one of ordinary people doing extraordinary things given half a chance. This virus is tough. But together and as a nation ‚Äî we're tougher.

I know we‚Äôll get through this and we‚Äôll be stronger for it, I promise you. Keep the faith. https://t.co/dC8JvRWPMC

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The stakes in this election have never been higher. We have to come together and beat Donald Trump.

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
This virus can hit anyone ‚Äî regardless of race, economic status, or access to power ‚Äî but it doesn‚Äôt impact every community equally. It hits hardest those who are most vulnerable and who have the fewest resources.

We have to do better for all our people. https://t.co/fx76CcIPdU

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The devastating unemployment numbers have made one thing even clearer: We need a fourth coronavirus relief package, and we need it fast. We need to take extraordinary steps to protect American families and ensure those laid off are made financially whole. https://t.co/PBOyM1JiUu

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
This morning's news of another rise in unemployment claims‚Äîon top of the millions already filed‚Äîis devastating. We have to make sure those affected get the benefits they deserve, but we can't stop there.

I'm announcing two new policies to help Americans get the relief they need: https://t.co/fUlIB2Fra2

Name: Joe Biden
Text: I can't believe I have to say this, but we should be expanding the number of testing sites and surging the number of tests ‚Äî not reducing them. Testing is key to finding a way out of this crisis. https://t.co/jj6ftCxVQt

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
We have to do more to ease the economic burden on working people. So today, I'm adopting two new policies to help deliver relief. As president, I will:

- Lower Medicare eligibility to age 60
- Forgive student debt for low-income and middle class families https://t.co/wtMnhJdCaR

Name: Joe Biden
Text: Let me be clear: No one should have to pay for their coronavirus treatment.

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
Eleven-year-old Isaac Johnston asked me what else kids should be doing in addition to washing their hands and staying home. My advice was simple:

- Stay a safe distance from friends
- Sneeze into your elbow
- And eat your vegetables https://t.co/ksPS4Xb7Wm

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
A total of about 17 million people have filed for unemployment over the last three weeks. This is unprecedented. 

The economic devastation that families all across this country are experiencing is not their fault. We've got to take extraordinary steps to protect them. https://t.co/2EfSIYXkLt

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We're seeing the soul of our nation on full display every day in this crisis ‚Äî and it makes me so proud to be an American. https://t.co/PERwpmeL2X

Name: Joe Biden
Text: If we come together, we will defeat Donald Trump. And when we do that, we will not only do the hard work of rebuilding this nation ‚Äî we will transform it.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: This nation has never been defeated when we‚Äôre together. And we‚Äôre not going to be defeated now.

Name: Joe Biden

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The coronavirus is not Donald Trump's fault, but the slow and chaotic response to it is. He's the commander in chief ‚Äî it's time he steps up, takes responsibility, and does his job. https://t.co/UFM5lPyzU3

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
The primary is over, but we're just getting started. We're building a campaign to defeat Donald Trump and ensure that America finally lives up to our founding promises ‚Äî but we can't do it without your help.

If you're with us, chip in today: https://t.co/bEBrI6DSqs

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
In the wake of COVID-19, working families across the country are facing a whole new set of challenges. This afternoon, I'll be hosting a town hall to listen to folks' concerns and discuss what we should be doing to deliver relief.

Tune in at 5:30 PM ET: https://t.co/xk0GcSpr50 https://t.co/Xzgoj0E4vB

Name: Joe Biden
Text: Together we will defeat Donald Trump. But we will also address the climate crisis. We will make college affordable. And we will make health care available to all.  We will not just rebuild this nation ‚Äì we‚Äôll transform it. And I‚Äôm asking you to join me. https://t.co/vJXlroCdDd

Name: Joe Biden
Text: And to Bernie‚Äôs supporters: I know that I need to earn your votes. And I know that might take time. But I want you to know that I see you, I hear you, and I understand the urgency of this moment. I hope you'll join us. You're more than welcome: You're needed.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We know how hard this is. You have put the interest of the nation ‚Äì and the need to defeat Donald Trump ‚Äì above all else. And for that we‚Äôre grateful. But we want you to know: we‚Äôll be reaching out. You‚Äôll be heard by me. As you say: Not me, Us.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: To Bernie and Jane, as friends, from Jill and me: You haven‚Äôt just run a political campaign; you‚Äôve created a movement. And make no mistake about it, we believe it‚Äôs a movement that is as powerful today as it was yesterday. That‚Äôs a good thing for our nation and our future.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: I know Bernie well. He‚Äôs a good man, a great leader, and one of the most powerful voices for change in our country. And it‚Äôs hard to sum up his contributions to our politics in one, single tweet. So I won‚Äôt try to. https://t.co/Z6OkCDWFNm

Name: Joe Biden
Text: As Jewish families across America and around the world prepare to observe the first night of Passover, Jill and I want to say chag sameach, and offer our very best wishes, to all who are celebrating. https://t.co/Qg5Wa9ftyT

Name: Joe Biden
Text: It is a national disgrace that our health care workers still don't have the protective equipment they need. Donald Trump needs to fully use the power of the Defense Production Act to deliver these life-saving supplies. https://t.co/VrjN3fAkHi

Name: Joe Biden
Text: We‚Äôre starting to see evidence that long-term exposure to air pollution‚Äîwhich disproportionately affects communities of color & low-income communities‚Äîis linked to COVID-19 death rates. It's past time we treat pollution like the threat to our health it is. https://t.co/3GD15s3xSy

Name: Joe Biden
Text: The weeks ahead will be some of the toughest we‚Äôve ever experienced as a nation. We need to face them with the same spirit and resolve that have guided us through previous crises. Because out of every trial and tribulation, America has always emerged stronger ‚Äî and we will again.

Name: Joe Biden
Text:
Folks, I know these are tough times, but this crisis has made it clearer than ever how much elections matter ‚Äî and what a difference it makes who is in the White House. If you can, please chip in to fuel our campaign. I would really appreciate it. 
https://t.co/mZbSSmDbN2

Name: Joe Biden
Text: @blackenterprise Jill and I send our heartfelt condolences to the entire Graves family. As the founder of Black Enterprise, Earl Graves Sr. was a trailblazer in his own right, a leader in the American business community, and paved the way for many Black entrepreneurs to realize their dreams.

Name: Joe Biden
Text: On #WorldHealthDay, we thank the tireless health care workers fighting COVID-19, and we see clearly why protecting the health of Americans requires U.S. global leadership‚Äîto coordinate an international response, strengthen health systems everywhere, and prevent the next pandemic.
